Build a Progressive Web App messenger designed for real-time multimodal and text
communication with LLMs. Below is the full specification.


Always Messenger
---

## CORE INTERACTION MODES

### Push-to-Activate Mode
- Bottom-anchored UI with a push-to-activate button
- Small spectrograph mouth display positioned just above the button
- Microphone activates on press; ASR result is sent after VAD closes
- Text thread bubbles visible in this mode

### Live Mode
- Large spectrograph mouth centered on screen
- Text bubbles hidden — mouth is the only feedback surface
- Camera button and text input bar visible at bottom
- When camera is active, sending a prompt attaches the current frame to the request

---

## SPECTROGRAPH MOUTH

- Visualizes TTS audio output as a spectrograph
- Mirrored on both X and Y axes to form a symmetrical mouth shape
- Color: continuously flowing rainbow gradient with subtle randomization 
  (avoid mechanical periodicity — inject perlin noise or randomized hue drift)
- Active only during TTS playback

---

## AUDIO PIPELINE

### ASR
- VAD (Voice Activity Detection) with configurable sensitivity
- Two modes: push-to-activate and live/interrupt mode
- Live mode supports VAD interrupt handling mid-TTS playback

### TTS
- Support Kokoro and Vibe Voice Realtime
- Both via OpenAI API-compatible TTS endpoints
- Configurable playback speed via Settings

---

## LLM INTEGRATION

Support the following endpoint types:
- OpenAI API standard (chat completions, streaming)
- LETTA streaming voice agent endpoints
- Local inference: LM Studio and Ollama (OpenAI-compatible)
- Vision-capable models: attach images to requests when supported

---

## SETTINGS MENU

Accessible via dropdown or dedicated settings panel. Configurable options:

**LLM Config**
- Endpoint type selector (OpenAI / LETTA / Local)
- Base URL, model name, API key

**TTS Config**
- Provider selector (Kokoro / Vibe Voice)
- Endpoint URL
- Playback speed slider

**Audio Config**
- VAD sensitivity slider
- Interrupt threshold

Settings persist to the active Contact Card (see below).

---

## CONTACTS & CONVERSATIONS

### Contact Cards
- Stored internally within the app
- Each contact contains:
  - Name, avatar
  - LLM configuration (endpoint, model, parameters)
  - System instructions for that LLM persona
  - Associated chat history

### Group Threads
- Support for group text threads with multiple contacts/LLM configs

---

## MEMORY SYSTEM

### Rolling Context
- Basic sliding window of recent messages passed as context
- Configurable window size

### Chat Summarizer
- UI: message range selector (0–100 slider selecting message indices)
- Triggers a separate inference call (outside chat completions) to produce 
  a dense summary
- Two output modes:
  1. **Polaroid Mode** — generates a vivid image generation prompt; a 
     snapshot that captures the feeling, atmosphere, and key moment of the 
     conversation as if photographed
  2. **Memory Mode** — produces a dense narrative summary capturing themes, 
     concepts, emotional tone, and underlying meaning; suitable for long-term 
     context tracking

### Seed Crystal / New Chat
When starting a new chat thread, two options:

1. **New Chat from Current** — runs as much of the current thread as fits 
   the context window through inference; produces a dense ~2000 character 
   seed crystal that encapsulates the conversation's trajectory, tone, and 
   key content; seeds the new thread
   
2. **New Chat from Single Response** — creates a new thread initialized 
   with only a single selected message as the starting point

---

## IMAGE SUPPORT

- Camera button in both modes
- In Live Mode with camera active: prompt sends current camera frame 
  attached to the LLM request (vision models only)
- Manual image attach in Push-to-Activate mode
- UI should gracefully disable vision features for non-vision models

---

## TECH CONSTRAINTS & PREFERENCES

- Progressive Web App (installable, offline-capable where possible)
- Modular architecture: separate modules for audio pipeline, LLM client, 
  TTS client, state management, UI
- All audio processing should be non-blocking
- Settings and contact data persisted to IndexedDB or localStorage
- Responsive design; primarily designed for mobile-first but functional on desktop